For a darkly comic romp through Vietnam combat and PTSD -- I know, I know, hard to fathom -- I recommend everyone (or at least every vet) read &quot;Veterans Day,&quot; by Rod Kane.  Joseph Heller (and he should know) called it &quot;the Catch-22 of the Vietnam War.&quot;<br>
--Jeff Stein<br>
(author, &quot;A Murder in Wartime: The Untold Spy Story that Changed the Course of the Vietnam War, St. Martin's Press, 1992)
